bios.aboutMe: I'm a pretty cool guy who likes to play GameCube in front of people. Strong believer in the 5-meals-a day-system.

experiences.instruments: Turntables, Moog Sub Phatty, Virtual Instruments via MPK249 MIDI controller
experiences.memory: This show was at an annual festival at Indiana State University. We performed in front of about 2000 people

experiences.summary: I played a solo DJ gig at the Purple Building in East Nashville
experiences.instruments: PT-01 Portable Turntable, NI S4 MkII DJ controller
experiences.memory: This was a fun one. Lots of electronic and hip hop music. The crowd was on the smaller size but got down! I debuted my first EP and everyone responded really well to it! Guud Vibez

experiences.summary: I performed with my electronic rock trio at The End in Nashville. You gotta play the end for 15 people at some point if you are a musician in this town!
experiences.instruments: PLX-1000 Turntable for scratching, MPK249 to trigger virtual instruments, Moog Sub Phatty
experiences.memory: This was a show that was badly promoted, and the low end at this joint is not for this style of music, but it was super fun and we got to jam for our work buddies!

experiences.summary: The Verve night club in Terre Haute Indiana is always poppin' till 3am on the weekends. My electronic trio came with the sauce that night which landed us a much larger festival gig
experiences.instruments: One Turntable for scratching, MPK249 for launching samples and virtual instruments, I actually did some backup vox but it was rap lol
experiences.memory: This was the first real club I ever played at. Existing in such college town with nothing else to do, this drew in a full house the Saturday night we performed on. A couple buddies went up and we got super drunk for free. My friend drove us back to Nashville at 4am

gearItems.model: PT-01 Scratch - Fully Customized with Jesse Dean Designs Parts
